<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,293,655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,317,554,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[325,489,554,579]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confinis">
<emphasis box="[325,489,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Lixus confinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Capiomont, 1875" authorityName="Capiomont" authorityYear="1875" box="[772,1140,554,580]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraatzi" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis box="[772,926,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Lixus kraatzi</emphasis>
Capiomont, 
<number box="[1079,1140,554,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1875.0">1875</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1153,1235,554,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1153,1235,554,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
This species can be easily recognized by a hook shaped, produced apex of aedeagus, distinctly divergent claws, curved rostrum, and densely puncturated pronotum.
</paragraph>
